35 (a)(A) “Conversion therapy” means providing professional services for the purpose of attempting
36 to change a person’s sexual orientation or gender identity, including attempting to change behaviors
37 or expressions of self or to reduce sexual or romantic attractions or feelings toward individuals of
38 the same gender.
39 (B) “Conversion therapy” does not mean:
40 (i) Counseling that assists a client who is seeking to undergo a gender transition or who is in
41 the process of undergoing a gender transition; or
42 (ii) Counseling that provides a client with acceptance, support and understanding, or counseling
43 that facilitates a client’s coping, social support and identity exploration or development, including
44 counseling in the form of sexual orientation-neutral or gender identity-neutral interventions provided
45 for the purpose of preventing or addressing unlawful conduct or unsafe sexual practices, as long as
